# Website & SEO for a Toronto Window Glass Repair Business

**Window & Glass Repair · Toronto & GTA**

Outcome: Recovered from a site compromised by injected adult, gambling, and crypto spam content, then rebuilt for local SEO dominance. 100+ additional converted leads within 3 months. Ranking #1 for "window replacement." Ongoing partnership now expanding into Voice AI.

---

## Client Background

[OhMyGlass](https://www.ohmyglass.ca) is a Toronto-based glass repair and replacement specialist with over 10 years of experience serving residential and commercial clients across the GTA. Known for their repair-first approach that saves customers 60 to 80% compared to full replacement, they offer 24/7 emergency availability and hold a 5-star reputation on Google and Facebook. Despite strong word-of-mouth and a decade of local credibility, the business had become nearly invisible online due to a serious technical problem they had not yet fully diagnosed.

---

## Challenge

By the time OhMyGlass came to Ed & Sy, their website had been quietly compromised. Malicious third-party content, including adult content, cryptocurrency promotions, gambling pages, and multilingual spam, had been injected throughout the site. The consequences were severe. Google had effectively deindexed the business for its core services, while a bogus page was outranking everything related to actual glass repair.

Organic leads had dried up entirely. The site was generating no meaningful traffic from search, and the brand's hard-earned reputation was at risk every time a potential customer stumbled across the injected content. Previous web providers had left the site vulnerable and had never addressed the underlying compromise. OhMyGlass needed more than a refresh. They needed a full recovery.

---

## Our Approach

**Step 1: Full site recovery**

Ed & Sy began with a thorough technical audit of the site's health. Every piece of injected and malicious content was identified and removed. Compromised page structures were cleaned, and root causes were addressed to prevent re-infection. A backlink audit and disavow process was initiated to repair the site's standing with Google.

**Step 2: Full website redesign**

With the site clean, we rebuilt it from the ground up, not just cosmetically but structurally. New service pages were built to clearly communicate OhMyGlass's full range of offerings. A dedicated set of location pages was developed to capture high-intent searches across the GTA's key service areas. Site speed, Core Web Vitals, and mobile performance were all optimized to meet modern search standards.

**Step 3: Local SEO rebuild**

The SEO strategy focused on rebuilding topical authority for the terms that drive real business: service-specific and geo-targeted keywords connecting OhMyGlass with customers actively searching for glass repair in their area. On-page SEO, meta structure, and Google Business Profile were all optimized for Toronto and GTA local search. The engagement ran on an initial 6-month contract, with measurable results appearing by the 3-month mark.

---

